                    <relation name="lawd:hasAttestation" ref="http://lawd.info/ontology/hasAttestation" active="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13306BaMaryam" passive="https://betamasaheft.eu/GCA837">
                    <desc>Baʾǝda Māryām is mentioned in the subscriptions and in the blessing formulae of the
                     manuscript <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/GCA837">Genoa, Castello d'Albertis, C.A. 837</ref>. His role is not clear, but his name is
                     associated with that of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13297Zamalakot">Zamalakot</persName>, who commissioned the
                     manuscript. Most likely Baʾǝda Māryām was also involved in commissioning the manuscript. The name of
                     Baʾǝda Māryām is associated in the same manuscript <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/GCA837">Genoa, Castello d'Albertis, C.A. 837</ref> also with the name of the scribe
                     <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13304GabAm">Gabra ʾAmlāk</persName>.</desc></relation>
                     <relation name="lawd:hasAttestation" ref="http://lawd.info/ontology/hasAttestation" active="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13306BaMaryam" passive="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESfbm003">
                     <desc>Baʾǝda Māryām is also mentioned in the subscriptions and in the blessing formulae of the
                     manuscript <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESfbm003">Gulo Maḵadā, Faqādā Māryām, FBM-003</ref> as commissioner of the manuscript.
                     His name is also here associated with that of the scribe <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13304GabAm">Gabra ʾAmlāk</persName>.</desc></relation>
                     <relation name="lawd:hasAttestation" ref="http://lawd.info/ontology/hasAttestation" active="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13306BaMaryam" passive="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESfbm001"/>
